#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an6.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.1:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Āhuneyyavagga "
msgstr "1. Worthy of Offerings "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Paṭhamaāhuneyyasutta "
msgstr "1. Worthy of Offerings (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.279, sc1
msgctxt "an6.1:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "an6.1:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

msgctxt "an6.1:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "an6.1:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.1:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "an6.1:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an6.1:2.1"
msgid "“Chahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a mendicant with six factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world. "

msgctxt "an6.1:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi chahi? "
msgstr "What six? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.1:2.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā neva sumano hoti na dummano, upekkhako viharati sato sampajāno. "
msgstr "It’s a mendicant who, when they see a sight with their eyes, is neither happy nor sad. They remain equanimous, mindful and aware. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.1:2.4"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … "
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.1:2.5"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … "
msgstr "When they smell an odor with their nose … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.1:2.6"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … "
msgstr "When they taste a flavor with their tongue … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.1:2.7"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … "
msgstr "When they feel a touch with their body … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.1:2.8"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya neva sumano hoti na dummano, upekkhako viharati sato sampajāno. "
msgstr "When they know a thought with their mind, they’re neither happy nor sad. They remain equanimous, mindful and aware. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.1:2.9"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, chahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant with these six factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an6.1:3.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "an6.1:3.2"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.1:3.3"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

